President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring April 2, 2016, as World Autism Awareness Day. In the proclamation, Obama reaffirms the commitment to providing equal opportunities and acceptance for individuals with autism spectrum disorder. He emphasizes that people with autism contribute to society in immeasurable ways and should be treated with respect and given the chance to reach their full potential. The Affordable Care Act ensures that individuals with autism have access to quality and affordable health insurance, and the administration is dedicated to improving educational opportunities and promoting inclusivity for individuals with autism. Obama also mentions the Autism CARES Act, which supports autism-related research, and the BRAIN Initiative, aimed at better understanding conditions like autism. The proclamation encourages all Americans to learn more about autism and support individuals on the autism spectrum and their families.